'''Planta Solar de Salamanca''' is a 13.8 peak MW [[photovoltaic]] [[power plant]] located in [[Salamanca]], [[Spain]].  The plant consists of approximately 70,000 [[Kyocera]] [[solar panel]]s, occupying approximately 36-[[hectare]] (89-[[acre]]) site.<ref name="kyocera">[http://global.kyocera.com/news/2007/0901.html Kyocera | News release<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>

The plant was opened for operation on September 18, 2007.<ref name="kyocera"/>

