{{Infobox organization |name = Bangladesh Rural Electrification Board |image = |image_border = |size = |alt = |caption = |map = |msize = |malt = |mcaption = |abbreviation = BREB |motto = |formation = 1977 |extinction = |type = Government |status = |purpose = |headquarters = [[Dhaka]], [[Bangladesh]] |location = |coords = <!-- Coordinates of location using a coordinates template --> |region_served = Bangladesh |members = |language = Bengali |leader_title = |leader_name = |main_organ = |parent_organization = |affiliations = |num_staff = |num_volunteers = |budget = |website = [http://www.reb.gov.bd/ Rural Electrification Board] |remarks = }}
'''Bangladesh Rural Electrification Board''' or BREB, is government owned and operated corporation in [[Dhaka]], [[Bangladesh]] and is responsible for rural electrification.<ref>{{cite web|title=Rural Electrification Board|url=http://en.banglapedia.org/index.php?title=Rural_Electrification_Board|website=en.banglapedia.org|publisher=Banglapedia|accessdate=11 October 2016}}</ref> It is major power distribution company in Bangladesh.<ref>{{cite web|title=Power Plants|url=http://en.banglapedia.org/index.php?title=Power_Plants|website=en.banglapedia.org|publisher=Banglapedia|accessdate=11 October 2016}}</ref> Major General [[Moin Uddin]] is the present chairman of the board.<ref>{{cite web|title=Kalsindur village lit up|url=http://en.prothom-alo.com/bangladesh/news/90023/Kalsindur-village-lit-up|website=Prothom Alo|accessdate=11 October 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Singapore to set up 1,400-MW plant at Maheshkhali - Energy Bangla|url=http://energybangla.com/singapore-to-set-up-1400-mw-plant-at-maheshkhali/|website=energybangla.com|publisher=Energy Bangla|accessdate=11 October 2016|date=9 December 2015}}</ref>
==History== Rural Electrification Board was established in 1977. It implements electrification of rural areas in Bangladesh and builds electrics lines and sub stations.<ref>{{cite web|title=Rural Electrification Board|url=http://en.banglapedia.org/index.php?title=Rural_Electrification_Board|website=en.banglapedia.org|publisher=Banglapedia|accessdate=11 October 2016}}</ref> It counterpart [[Bangladesh Power Development Board|Power Development Board]] manages electric distribution in urban areas.<ref>{{cite web|title=Power Development Board|url=http://en.banglapedia.org/index.php?title=Power_Development_Board|website=en.banglapedia.org|publisher=Banglapedia|accessdate=11 October 2016}}</ref> [[Palli Bidyut Samities]] in a subsidiary of the board and acts as a consumer cooperative.<ref>{{cite web|title=Rural Electrification|url=http://en.banglapedia.org/index.php?title=Rural_Electrification|website=en.banglapedia.org|publisher=Banglapedia|accessdate=11 October 2016}}</ref> The board has expanded rural electric connections rapidly. It has taken some market shares of solar energy.<ref>{{cite web|title=Solar energy dims as grid power expands|url=http://www.thedailystar.net/business/solar-energy-dims-grid-power-expands-1274971|website=thedailystar.net|publisher=The Daily Star|accessdate=11 October 2016|date=25 August 2016}}</ref>
