{{Infobox company | logo = http://www.sharcenergy.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/SHARC-International-Logo-amended.png | type = [[Public company|Public]] | industry = [[Energy]] [[HVAC]] | foundation = 2010 | founder = [[Lynn Lyle Mueller]] | location = [[Vancouver|Vancouver, British Columbia]], Canada | products = SHARC PIRANHA | homepage = http://www.sharcenergy.com }}
'''SHARC International Systems Inc.''' (CSE: SHRC), DBA SHARC Energy Systems, is a Canadian public corporation, based in Vancouver, British Columbia, that specializes in wastewater heat recovery.<ref name="nationalgeographic">{{cite web|url=http://news.nationalgeographic.com/news/energy/2012/12/121211-sewage-heat-recovery/|title=Waste Wattage: Cities Aim to Flush Heat Energy Out of Sewers|publisher=news.nationalgeographic.com|accessdate=2014-07-21}}</ref> Founded in 2010 by Lynn Mueller, the company operates throughout North America. A subsidiary, SHARC Energy Systems, based in Leicester, UK, operates throughout Europe.<ref name="nottinghampost">{{cite web|url=http://www.nottinghampost.com/Sewage-heat-sniffed-firm-heads-UK-jobs/story-21117754-detail/story.html|title=Sewage-to-heat not to be sniffed at as firm heads to UK with jobs &#124; Nottingham Post|publisher=nottinghampost.com|accessdate=2014-07-21}}</ref>
The company is one of only a few worldwide focusing on [[waste heat recovery unit|waste heat recovery]] as an [[alternative energy]] source, reducing the need to burn fossil fuels. Their systems can be used for domestic hot water production as well as building space heating & cooling.<ref name="theglobeandmail">{{cite web|url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/report-on-business/making-the-most-of-wastewater/article16121777/|title=Making the most of wastewater - The Globe and Mail|publisher=theglobeandmail.com|accessdate=2014-07-21}}</ref>
SHARC Energy's feature products are the SHARC™ and PIRANHA™, which remove solids from [[wastewater]], allowing the wastewater to effectively move through a heat exchanger and heat pump. The systems provide hot water heating, space heating, air conditioning, and wastewater cooling.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.waterworld.com/articles/wwi/print/volume-31/issue-2/technology-case-studies/piranhas-and-sharcs-unlocking-the-potential-of-wastewater-heat.html|title=PIRANHAS AND SHARCS - UNLOCKING THE POTENTIAL OF WASTEWATER HEAT|last=Williams|first=Andrew|date=|website=Water & Wastewater International|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref>
